    <abstract>
      <t>Lisp-Nexagon is a geospatial intelligence network protocol designed
to support physical-world applications such as transportation, public
safety, and logistics. It combines the Locator/ID Separation Protocol
(LISP) with the H3 spatial indexing system to enable distributed
agents to report, aggregate, and disseminate geospatial state
information.

	 </t>
